sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Booking Holdings Inc (Symbol: BKNG), where a total volume of 22,248 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 2.2 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 580.2% of BKNG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 383,455 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $2100 strike call option expiring May 11, 2018 , with 1,031 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 103,100 underlying shares of BKNG.

Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) saw options trading volume of 44,914 contracts, representing approximately 4.5 million underlying shares or approximately 102.3% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.4 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $182.50 strike put option expiring May 18, 2018 , with 7,410 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 741,000 underlying shares of HD.

Especially high volume was seen for the $302.50 strike call option expiring May 11, 2018 , with 860 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 86,000 underlying shares of REGN.
